Intressant nog föregriper BonJour den epistemiska dygdeteorin.
10 år innan den slår igenom skriver han:
.QS
.vs 12
.ps 10
The same conflict between perspectives which we have seen to arise in the process of epistemic assessment
can also arise with regard to the moral assessment of a person’s action:
the agent’s subjective conception of what he is doing may differ dramatically from that
which would in principle be available to an external observer who had access to facts
about the situation that are beyond the agent’s ken.
.QE
